Tool = script.Parent
local stillEquipped = false
function onEquippedLocal(mouse) stillEquipped = true if mouse == nil then return end while stillEquipped do mouse.Icon = "rbxasset://textures\\GunCursor.png" while Tool.Enabled and stillEquipped do wait(0.01) end mouse.Icon = "rbxasset://textures\\GunWaitCursor.png" while not Tool.Enabled and stillEquipped do wait(0.01) end end end
function onUnequippedLocal() stillEquipped = false end
Tool.Equipped:connect(onEquippedLocal) Tool.Unequipped:connect(onUnequippedLocal)

local Tool = script.Parent local Handle = Tool.Handle local Fire
local myCharacter local myHumanoid local Torso local RightShoulder local TargetPoint local TargetDir local TargetHorAngle local TargetVertAngle
local ProjectileScript
local newlyRunning = true -- Purpose of this boolean is to make the wait for the tool to be re-equipped -- a little less painful.
local StandardC1 = CFrame.new(-0.5, 0.5, 0) * CFrame.Angles(0, math.pi/2, 0)
function onActivated() if not Tool.Enabled then return end Tool.Enabled = false
myCharacter = Tool.Parent if myCharacter then myHumanoid = myCharacter:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") Torso = myCharacter:FindFirstChild("Torso") if Torso then RightShoulder = Torso:FindFirstChild("Right Shoulder") end if myHumanoid and RightShoulder then -- Bring arm up, to prepare to throw dagger. -- Standard shoulder C1 is StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(0, 0, 0), so we use that as the -- starting point. -- Upright is StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(0, 0, -math.pi/2), so we use that as the endpoint -- and interpolate between. for i = 1, 15 do RightShoulder.C1 = StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(0, 0, -i * math.pi/30) wait() end wait(0.1)
-- Calculate target direction and corresponding horizontal angle. -- But make sure we're not throwing behind us (even though that would -- be cool). The limit is throwing directly to the side. TargetPoint = myHumanoid.TargetPoint TargetDir = Torso.CFrame:pointToObjectSpace(TargetPoint) - Vector3.new(1, 0.5, 0) TargetVertAngle = math.atan(TargetDir.Y / TargetDir.Z) if TargetDir.Z > 0 then if TargetDir.X > 0 then TargetHorAngle = math.pi/2 else TargetHorAngle = -math.pi/2 end else TargetHorAngle = math.atan(TargetDir.X / TargetDir.magnitude) end
-- Meanwhile, down angle is at StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(TargetHorAngle, 0, TargetVertAngle), so we again -- interpolate to bring the arm down. for i = 1, 5 do wait() RightShoulder.C1 = StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(i * TargetHorAngle / 5, 0, (i-5) * math.pi/10 + i * TargetVertAngle / 5) end
-- Now, fire off a projectile.
ProjectileScript = Tool:FindFirstChild("BDProjScript") if ProjectileScript then TargetPos = Tool:FindFirstChild("TargetPos") if TargetPos and myHumanoid then TargetPos.Value = myHumanoid.TargetPoint -- Necessary to send this since server only updates TargetPoint on mouse click. end ProjectileScript = ProjectileScript:Clone() ProjectileScript.Parent = Tool ProjectileScript.Disabled = false end
-- And bring your arm back to normal. wait(0.2) for i = 10, 0, -1 do wait() RightShoulder.C1 = StandardC1 * CFrame.Angles(i * TargetHorAngle/10, 0, 0) end else Tool.Enabled = true end else Tool.Enabled = true end end
function onEquipped() if newlyRunning and not Tool.Enabled then wait(5) Tool.Enabled = true end newlyRunning = false end
function onUnequipped() Handle.Transparency = 0.0 Fire = Handle:FindFirstChild("Fire") if Fire then Fire.Enabled = true end if RightShoulder then RightShoulder.C1 = StandardC1 end if not Tool.Enabled then wait(5) Tool.Enabled = true end end
Tool.Activated:connect(onActivated) Tool.Equipped:connect(onEquipped) Tool.Unequipped:connect(onUnequipped)

local Tool = script.Parent local Handle = Tool.Handle
local InitRotVel local InitVel
local myCharacter = Tool.Parent local myHumanoid local myPlayer
local Target = Tool:FindFirstChild("TargetPos") if Target then Target = Target.Value else if myCharacter then myHumanoid = myCharacter:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") if myHumanoid then Target = myHumanoid.TargetPoint end end end
if not Target then script:Remove() end
local daggerReturning = false local ctr = 0
local debris = game:GetService("Debris")
local Dagger = Handle:Clone() Dagger.Transparency = 0.0 Dagger.CFrame = Handle.CFrame local DaggerPos = Dagger.Position local VelVector = Target - Dagger.Position InitVel = 100 * VelVector.unit Dagger.Velocity = InitVel InitRotVel = 20 * Dagger.CFrame.lookVector Dagger.RotVelocity = InitRotVel Dagger.Name = "BoomerangDaggerProjectile"
local Fire = Handle:FindFirstChild("Fire") if Fire then Fire.Enabled = false end Handle.Transparency = 1.0
local AntiGrav = Instance.new("BodyForce") AntiGrav.force = Vector3.new(0, 196.2 * Dagger:GetMass(), 0) AntiGrav.Parent = Dagger
local WhipSound local ThudSound local soundCo
Dagger.Parent = game.Workspace
Tool.Unequipped:connect(function() if ThudSound then ThudSound:Stop() end Dagger:Remove() script:Remove() end)
function tagHumanoid(humanoid, player) local CreatorTag = Instance.new("ObjectValue") CreatorTag.Name = "creator" CreatorTag.Value = player CreatorTag.Parent = humanoid end
function untagHumanoid(humanoid) if not humanoid then return end local Tag = humanoid:FindFirstChild("creator") if Tag then Tag:Remove() end end
function blow(hit) if hit:FindFirstChild("BoomerangDaggerRecentlyHit") then return else local DebounceTag = Instance.new("BoolValue") DebounceTag.Name = "BoomerangDaggerRecentlyHit" DebounceTag.Parent = hit debris:AddItem(DebounceTag, 0.3)
local hitThing = hit.Parent if not hitThing then return end if hitThing.ClassName == "Hat" then hitThing = hitThing.Parent end
local myCharacter = Tool.Parent if not myCharacter then return end
local hitHumanoid = hitThing:FindFirstChild("Humanoid") if hitThing ~= myCharacter and hitHumanoid ~= nil then myPlayer = game.Players:GetPlayerFromCharacter(myCharacter) tagHumanoid(hitHumanoid, myPlayer) hitHumanoid:TakeDamage(12) wait(1) untagHumanoid(hitHumanoid) elseif hitThing == Tool and daggerReturning then Dagger:Remove() wait() -- To avoid an error Dagger = nil end end end
function manageSound() WhipSound = Dagger:FindFirstChild("WhipSound") if WhipSound then WhipSound:Play() wait(5/30) WhipSound:Play() wait(7/30) WhipSound:Play() wait(10/30) WhipSound:Play() wait(17/30) WhipSound:Play() wait(17/30) if Dagger then WhipSound:Play() wait(10/30) end if Dagger then WhipSound:Play() wait(7/30) end while Dagger do WhipSound:Play() wait(5/30) end end end
soundCo = coroutine.create(manageSound) coroutine.resume(soundCo)
Dagger.Touched:connect(blow)
for i = 50, 0, -1 do Dagger.Velocity = i/50 * InitVel Dagger.RotVelocity = i/50 * InitRotVel wait() end
daggerReturning = true
while Handle and Dagger do Dagger.Velocity = 2 * ctr * (Handle.Position - Dagger.Position).unit Dagger.RotVelocity = -ctr/50 * InitRotVel ctr = ctr + 1 wait() end
Tool.Enabled = true Handle.Transparency = 0.0 if Fire then Fire.Enabled = true end ThudSound = Handle:FindFirstChild("ThudSound") if ThudSound then ThudSound:Play() end
wait(0.3) -- (for sound to finish) script:Remove()
